HEADWORD: Amphineura
<hw>Am`phi*neu"ra</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. <grk>'amfi`</grk> + <?/ sinew, nerve.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A division of Mollusca remarkable for the bilateral symmetry of the
organs and the arrangement of the nerves.</def>⟦br⟧
